a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">What Danco and=
 Hsu both realized in two steps is: </p><ol style=3D"margin: 1em 0;"><li st=
yle=3D"margin: 3.75px 0 3.75px 7.5px; mso-special-format: bullet;"><p style=
=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0;">There s=
hould be a better way to finance recurring revenue businesses. </p></li><li=
 style=3D"margin: 3.75px 0 3.75px 7.5px; mso-special-format: bullet;"><p st=
yle=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0;">Pipe=
 is that better way. Even better than debt.</p></li></ol><p style=3D"color:=
 #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">Pipe solv=
es the problem that both Hsu and Danco alluded to: right now, the way that =
startups fund themselves doesn&#8217;t match their business models or matur=
ity. Product-Market Fit gets most of the headlines. Product-Founder Fit is =
an up-and-comer. But <strong>Business-Funding Fit</strong> -- funding each =
business with the right type of capital -- is an equally important piece of=
 the puzzle when it comes to generating outsized returns over time. </p><p =
style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1e=
m 0;">As we discussed in <em><a href=3D"https://email.mg2.substack.com/c/eJ=
xVkM2OhCAQhJ9GbmMAxZ8Dh7nsaxiUVtlBcKDZHd9-0Ul2swmEpCvF11WTQlh8OOTuI5IUIQxGS=
9bwrhJ1T7SsNetER0wc5gCwKWMlhgRkT6M1k0Lj3eWglAuySsGauRUatK4op6JR_QwzFaxv667l=
3UhOzqCSNuAmkPAF4fAOiJUr4h6L6l7wj3ycx9EH45YypjGimh7l5Lcs7Pni6XV4wxVuyaLZcoi=
bTxiNhkCM5BnNKO8ZF1XVlKx8Lq_H8txfn6Ko6bbwf5-SIH9pWX6sagN7CTnjkN8tOYPHAE6NFv=
Q7Pr4Lu9LgsYN08B0tIOYFruHZiajapm45yTTtc3XuD_QDffSCYA" style=3D"color: #1a1a=
1a; text-decoration: underline;">Tencent: The Ultimate Outsider</a></em>, W=
ill Thorndike analyzed eight of the businesses that most outperformed their=
 peers and the market over decades in his book, <em>The Outsiders</em>. The=
 thing that they all had in common was that their CEOs were all excellent c=
apital allocators. They were thoughtful about how they funded their busines=
ses and how they spent the money they had. </p><p style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; =
font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">Not every CEO is a =
great capital allocator. Most aren&#8217;t. But in an <a href=3D"https://em=
ail.mg2.substack.com/c/eJxFkM2SgyAMx5-m3HAURPHAoZd9DQckKlsFC7Gtb79oDzvD5INM=
8k9-g0aYQjzUFhKSPUHsnVVVwyQXdUesqm0lhSQu9WMEWLVbFMYdyLabxQ0aXfBXR1kyQWbVGmF=
M0xhpRi5Fx2QnuGZjx2UtRVNrcur0ercO_AAKXhCP4IEsakbc0o3fb-wnP73Ax2o_hGIIa85Zyc=
rsyvaMZTYOE_UBqQWD9EwMIEKk2lPnc_By8KZvhzOddYwHnfeYkIaRbm6D3E-cOmdWJesqJjhvi=
