 style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1=
em 0;">That&#8217;s enterprise value that I, as a beleaguered shareholder, =
would love to have in my pocket.</p><h3 style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font-famil=
y: 'SF Compact Display', -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, 'Segoe UI', Rob=
oto, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif, 'Apple Color Emoji', 'Segoe UI Emoji', '=
Segoe UI Symbol'; font-size: 1.375em; font-weight: 700; line-height: 1.16em=
; margin: 1em 0 0.625em 0;"><strong>Why Now: Pipe&#8217;s Flywheel </strong=
></h3><p style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margi=
n: 0 0 1em 0;">By now, we&#8217;ve established that Pipe should exist. It&#=
8217;s a brilliant idea that helps businesses fund themselves more efficien=
tly and gives investors access to a new asset class that strips out all of =
the noise and directs those sweet, sweet recurring revenue cash flows right=
 into their veins. </p><p style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-he=
ight: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">But it&#8217;s fucking hard to start a new =
asset class on a new exchange. It&#8217;s a two-sided marketplace problem: =
you need to both convince companies to sell their revenues and investors to=
 buy them. That&#8217;s part of the reason that Pipe has raised so much mon=
ey for a company its size. When Pipe announced its seed extension, Hurst hi=
ghlighted this challenge: </p><blockquote style=3D"border-left: 4px solid #=
67bdfc; margin: 1em 0;"><p style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-h=
eight: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0; margin-left: 1em;"><em>We are connecting Sa=
aS companies with investors, and in order to do that, liquidity needs to be=
 in the marketplace. Only a small portion of the new financing will go to c=
ore operations&#8212;we run lean and mean&#8212;and a vast majority of the =
money will go into the marketplace, so as more SaaS companies sign up, ther=
e will be liquidity.</em></p></blockquote><p style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font-=
size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">This is what the challen=
ge looks like in practice: </p><ul style=3D"margin: 1em 0;"><li style=3D"ma=
rgin: 3.75px 0 3.75px 7.5px; mso-special-format: bullet;"><p style=3D"color=
: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0;">Pipe needs to si=
multaneously attract companies willing to sell their recurring revenue and =
investors willing to buy it.</p></li><li style=3D"margin: 3.75px 0 3.75px 7=
=2E5px; mso-special-format: bullet;"><p=20=
style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 1=
6px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0;">If it attracts a lot of companies and f=
ew investors, there will be more supply than demand and investors&#8217; bi=
ds will be low - maybe they would pay $0.70 for $1 worth of revenue. </p></=
li><li style=3D"margin: 3.75px 0 3.75px 7.5px; mso-special-format: bullet;"=
><p style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0;=
">If bids are low, companies will leave and find better ways to fund the bu=
siness, including offering bigger discounts to entice customers to pay upfr=
ont. </p></li><li style=3D"margin: 3.75px 0 3.75px 7.5px; mso-special-forma=
t: bullet;"><p style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px;=
 margin: 0;">If Pipe attracts a lot of investors but few companies, there w=
on&#8217;t be enough recurring revenue streams for investors to buy, and it=
 will remain small. </p></li></ul><p style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16=
px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">One way to solve that in the ear=
ly days is by buying liquidity - supporting the market by either buying rec=
urring revenue streams itself or by paying more to bring companies onto the=
 platform. Pipe is good enough at what it does, and well-financed enough, t=
hat it would have solved the chicken-and-egg problem either way, it just wo=
uld have cost a lot upfront. </p><p style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16p=
x; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">The only thing better than being =
good, though, is being good <em>and</em> lucky. Almost all of the factors t=
hat I wrote about in <em><a href=3D"https://email.mg2.substack.com/c/eJxVkM=
FuhSAQRb9GdhoEUVyw6Ka_YVBGpSr4YOx7_n15mrRpwoRkbmbO3DtohMmHU-0-IjkihM4aVdZMc=
lG1xKjKlFJIYmM3BoBN21VhOIDsR7_aQaP17pqglAkyK1lKkLKpG0kbzkVdyZZS2o8tNwLMKMmb=
0-nDWHADKPiGcHoHZFUz4h4z_pGxz_Scx94H66YiHn1EPSzF4Lck7KmiH_GpA-Q25pBOcFOOM-S=
bDgtgJFYxymhJWVsywXldlMVjei3TY399iayi28T-bSVB_eKSvMx6g_USksku_dvhLJ4dON2vYG=
7_eCd22cFzB-XgGVdAhHA336EI3tRVw0iiGZ-yc3-gH0JuggI" style=3D"color: #1a1a1a;=
 text-decoration: underline;">Software is Eating the Markets</a></em> are c=
oming together to smash through Pipe&#8217;s liquidity challenge.  </p><ul =
style=3D"margin: 1em 0;"><li style=3D"margin: 3.75px 0 3.75px 7.5px; mso-sp=
ecial-format: bullet;"><p style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-he=
ight: 26px; margin: 0;">SaaS and subscription businesses, from Zoom to Pelo=
ton to paid newsletters, are growing incredibly fast during COVID, creating=
 more supply of recurring revenue streams. </p></li><li style=3D"margin: 3.=
75px 0 3.75px 7.5px; mso-special-format: bullet;"><p style=3D"color: #1a1a1=
a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0;">Interest rates are at al=
l-time lows, and investors are looking for yield.</p></li><li style=3D"marg=
in: 3.75px 0 3.75px 7.5px; mso-special-format: bullet;"><p style=3D"color: =
#1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0;">Investors are part=
icularly interested in SaaS and subscription business companies as evidence=
d by their equities&#8217; outperformance in the market, and are more than =
happy to buy exposure to the cash flows directly without paying a huge mult=
iple.</p></li><li style=3D"margin: 3.75px 0 3.75px 7.5px; mso-special-forma=
t: bullet;"><p style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px;=
 margin: 0;">Pipe sits right in the middle of those two, providing an excha=
nge on which companies can earn cash today and investors can buy the revenu=
e streams they want. </p></li><li style=3D"margin: 3.75px 0 3.75px 7.5px; m=
so-special-format: bullet;"><p style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; li=
ne-height: 26px; margin: 0;">More liquidity means more transactions, which =
builds trust in the asset class, and more bids competing for revenue stream=
s means better bids, which attracts more companies.</p></li></ul><p style=
=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;"=
>This is Pipe&#8217;s flywheel and network effect: more bids &#8594; better=
 prices &#8594; more companies &#8594; more bids.</p><table class=3D"image-=
