le=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0=
;">Pipe is the cheapest and most efficient capital for SaaS and subscriptio=
n businesses today. The beauty of a marketplace or exchange, though, is tha=
t once you get it going, it just keeps getting better over time. As Pipe co=
ntinues to turn the flywheel, it will become even more of a no-brainer tool=
 in the SaaS and subscription business financing toolkit. And it&#8217;s ju=
st getting started&#8230; </p><h1 style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font-family: 'SF=
 Compact Display', -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, 'Segoe UI', Roboto, H=
elvetica, Arial, sans-serif, 'Apple Color Emoji', 'Segoe UI Emoji', 'Segoe =
UI Symbol'; font-size: 2em; font-weight: 700; line-height: 1.16em; margin: =
1em 0 0.625em 0;"><strong>Matching Financing to Businesses </strong></h1><p=
 style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1=
em 0;">Pipe is just getting started. </p><ul style=3D"margin: 1em 0;"><li s=
tyle=3D"margin: 3.75px 0 3.75px 7.5px; mso-special-format: bullet;"><p styl=
e=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0;">First,=
 it focused just on SaaS businesses. </p></li><li style=3D"margin: 3.75px 0=
 3.75px 7.5px; mso-special-format: bullet;"><p style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; fon=
t-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0;">Then, it opened up to all subs=
cription businesses. </p></li><li style=3D"margin: 3.75px 0 3.75px 7.5px; m=
so-special-format: bullet;"><p style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; li=
ne-height: 26px; margin: 0;">Next, Pipe is developing a Recurring Revenue O=
ffering that allows companies to pre-sell future subscription revenue to ra=
ise even more money. </p></li><li style=3D"margin: 3.75px 0 3.75px 7.5px; m=
so-special-format: bullet;"><p style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; li=
ne-height: 26px; margin: 0;">In the future, Pipe will provide a greater and=
 greater number of financing alternatives custom built for tech businesses.=
 </p></li></ul><p style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26=
px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">Pipe is in the business of creating Business-Fundin=
g Fit. Its skills -- pulling in companies&#8217; financial data via APIs, a=
ssigning ratings based on that data, attracting investors, providing liquid=
ity, and managing seamless ongoing financial transactions -- will be extens=
ible to many more subscription-based business models over time. </p><p styl=
e=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;=
">Think internet bills, cable bills, cell phone bills, membership fees, fit=
ness app memberships, creator economy subscriptions&#8230; if it&#8217;s a =
digital subscription, Pipe should be able to turn MRR into ARR and provide =
access to cheap, efficient capital. If I ever turn on paid subscriptions fo=
r Not Boring, Pipe is going to be my first call.  </p><p style=3D"color: #1=
a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">If you run a=
 SaaS or digital subscription business, <strong><a href=3D"https://email.mg=
2.substack.com/c/eJxFUMtuwyAQ_BpztHg6-MChUpXfsLDZOjQ2EFja-O9L4kOllVa7o9nZmc=
